 which I did not recognize as mine: “Stop, stop! How dare you, what right have you got? Of all the insulting—No, I won’t stand it! How dare you—Of my land, of my people … be silent! Be silent,” I cried ever louder: “You! … To dare tell me to my face that in Germany—Be silent!”

As it was, they had all been silent for a long time already—since that moment when, from the bang of my fist, the ring had started rolling. It rolled to the very end of the table; and was cautiously 